ing diagnostics**\\n\\nI'm thinking through how `getLowest` checks if TCCL is a child of the current class loader; if it is, it returns TCCL. If the blocking loader fails, I see that using `Class.forName(name)` via LogFactoryImpl succeeds, which is good! Next, I need to ensure that `getResource` and `getSystemResource` only run if diagnostics are enabled. I should check the diagnostics property in Commons Logging and maybe inspect the constants using `javap -v` or `strings`.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0117cd8f1f716fb20169f935a42f08819d826bf94543e6d0a6\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-TWrRqhAXse8oNQb0-KeMQtF76Rixemrd-RtYX39MN4vDW4Laa6EiepnZAI_hwxYXdTUto6WyxHilOJKkmQmMCNBBfg6TZ9ZXWtPlnvbkc2vDQ0_L1l80Y3xT6g-ZiPs3NrmvH0w_e7W-pbphmk_0KVUwmZ9oG0_si71PA92lZkuOcTLVOdzDHjSJLoHg33KzdNWTpJbTZ3geD6osxPTtFVdLepN11A8zE3qlj0d19SZf1w0ckr1Ew8dLwMx2Of5Sa8lZvAjUhkC23cXGvfTWBfqq-QeArti5iagqo8petUP40zzhIU0deMtEHpEJWZvEwa3J8KMrL4pPPfwC5KvfvZXFWdca-4OdIBw1sBl70_ZC_Wi9snKErsYMK5ppBzjS9xWA1O0-nlVi1YfEPt7yf_l6TBxAVV-Hz7MvMQrMCn6aJNM0XDDIcatw7ySVtLaCVKkx3R6fxLreOndVqEErGm2turq5-j0i2-H178I_PChHN4HyEM2XiW_E1u-TF0wDMVUjvoh74BOk6wPPRNB7SLxjzLx5r7WwWE_pJTwH0YEcD4bw6FaBdlDgFvIXj6hSIFdCXMIYt-P_sswPYVmJ03V9cK82zV4xCWORbCp7MsZIZyVzVIrz-HZ9E6cB8FTAP7ylBtNXUS4xA_TFEPwIK_gKSLaVjl1R4cL-wl6-DCk0SCM_BvliuAbR9iG7dXmSRFWyUEHjThAMZmHAIqVkwBeXd8tXofLHeEoL47ZOYhfnjQ41wVhTlJoiJwJTeHIfZl5yOdusG9x1bkfIoRGET-6zpZYwXeWsqtod-Rxzrx1w98qLHfQCP9WZRGjfDX7Qhop_837rsKmFOaWwIeMTYZIGLC6wvYmrpyijXUi5AtmlRxH58fxp_bP11HruLcp65Kw6R3ZDQbbTqDcM_7oHdz37HtvSstHZZi-fqyJ2U6SfUcZS4lohS0ZKubokrG7POHLNmvf3CFbdh-o9AI-23_gxK5BzZdvOQgRUjJmV45lfVnRZLNZyZ_EdqRG8m6AYDp_A5tHBT59RaC65l7PkPfIZW_7An_pKkNPktEwTAWpH_AmeMwT_HvfxDHfESsdhll-x-2fLefqjWvicPUUDoJA6J5DkFVzd902Pb7gPjNf-y6QCcmJDeEoJK4aOznsZIveigHx2xNVziP-gLIKirPJH0br5f5g-pu9s1v-hmXrX_qJgc1a6E589tF53TE7xDfG0y01yVloXOYqXI21aQwg_zy_Fe5gt1Sg4bQXCyRW1ikB2S3qWkd__vdVavaXltRjG53f0utZGR5Vvp_PUVXSsVLdxH8hMY8EmBZhRqKZEKiUhfBXkBn1NvQ1wSGt__ae5